# Branch workflow

- **Do not push commits directly to `develop` or to `main`.** The **Develop** repository ruleset includes **require a pull request before merging** for `refs/heads/develop`, so direct pushes to `develop` are **rejected**. Push to another **branch** and open a **PR into `develop`**, then merge to land work.
- **Clone / sync:** default branch is `develop` ‚Äî `git pull` on `develop`, then `git checkout -b feature/‚Ä¶` (or `fix/‚Ä¶`, `chore/‚Ä¶`) from the current tip.
- **`main`** is the release / production branch. Do not push to it directly (use PRs; `main` is further constrained by the **Main** ruleset and the merge guard below).
- **Pull requests into `main`:** only from `develop` (see `.github/workflows/merge-to-main-guard.yml`). Do not open PRs from `feature/‚Ä¶`, `fix/‚Ä¶`, or other head branches **into** `main`.
- **Releases:** when `develop` is ready, open **one** PR **`develop` ‚Üí `main`**. All feature work merges to `develop` first (branch ‚Üí `develop` PRs only).
- In GitHub **Settings ‚Üí Rules** / **Branches** for `main`, add the `develop ‚Üí main only` / Test checks as **required** so policy cannot be bypassed casually.
- Automation (e.g. Dependabot) that opens PRs into `main` from non-`develop` heads will fail the guard until `target-branch: develop` (or a documented exception in the guard workflow).
- `git config init.defaultBranch develop` is optional locally; the remote default branch on GitHub is `develop`.
